Rescue two children, nine vehicles Operatives of Rivers State Police Command have arrested a man, identified as Adamu Siraju, who was brandishing a rifle in Army uniform, on February 1, 2022, at a hotel in the Rumuigbo, Obio-Akpor area of Rivers State.  “Recall that on September 25, 2020, two little children were stolen from their mother in her shop, the children are Favour Boniface and Miracle Boniface, and two days ago, on February 23, 2022, we were able to rescue that little girl and arrested three suspects in connection with that matter.
 
“Favour Ajuzie, 30 stole the baby in conjunction with Chioma Chibuike, 43 and sold the baby to Comfort Abatuo, 56 and that child had been living with that woman since, until the child was rescued.”
  
The police boss further stated that the command had within  January and February arrested 11 suspected kidnappers, eight suspected armed robbers; three suspected child traffickers and recovered four arms, four locally-made guns, ten cartridges, two magazines, 44 ammunition and nine vehicles. 